"use strict";(self.webpackChunkhalt_website=self.webpackChunkhalt_website||[]).push([[30942],{30739:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"tag":{"label":"veterinary","permalink":"/docs/tags/veterinary","allTagsPath":"/docs/tags","count":22,"items":[{"id":"Rats/getting-started/rat-care-guide","title":"A Comprehensive Guide to Rat Care","description":"Rats are intelligent, social, and engaging pets that bring a unique joy to any home. To ensure they live long, happy, and healthy lives, it\u2019s essential to understand and meet their specific needs. This guide provides a comprehensive overview of daily and weekly care routines for your pet rats.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/getting-started/rat-care-guide"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/rat-respiratory-infections-uris-guide","title":"A Guide to Respiratory Infections (URIs) in Rats","description":"Respiratory illness is one of the most common health issues affecting pet rats. Nearly all domestic rats are carriers of Mycoplasma pulmonis, the primary bacterium responsible for these infections...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/rat-respiratory-infections-uris-guide"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bloat-in-guinea-pigs","title":"Bloat in Guinea Pigs","description":"Bloat, also known as Gastric Dilatation and Volvulus (GDV), is a sudden, life-threatening condition that can affect guinea pigs. It occurs when the stomach fills with gas and, in some cases, twists on itself (volvulus), cutting off blood supply to the stomach and other organs. This is a severe medical emergency that requires immediate veterinary intervention. Understanding the signs and acting quickly can be the difference between life and death.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bloat-in-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bordetella-in-guinea-pigs","title":"Bordetella in Guinea Pigs","description":"Bordetella bronchiseptica is a bacterium that causes respiratory disease in a variety of animals. While it is most commonly known as a cause of \'kennel cough\' in dogs, it can be a life-threatening...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/bordetella-in-guinea-pigs"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/cl","title":"Caseous/Cervical Lymphadenitis in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs are beloved pets known for their friendly and gentle nature, but like all animals, they can be susceptible to a variety of health issues. One condition that can affect them is Caseous Lymphadenitis (CL), a bacterial infection that causes swelling and abscesses in the lymph nodes. This disease can be serious and requires prompt treatment to avoid complications.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/cl"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/dental-disease","title":"Dental Disease in Guinea Pigs","description":"Dental disease is one of the most common and serious health problems affecting guinea pigs. Unlike humans, a guinea pig\'s teeth grow continuously throughout their life. This continuous growth can...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/dental-disease"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/diabetes-in-rats","title":"Diabetes in Rats","description":"Diabetes Mellitus is a condition in which the body either fails to produce enough insulin or cannot use it effectively, resulting in persistently high blood sugar (hyperglycemia). While not common in pet rats, it does occur \u2014 particularly in older or overweight individuals \u2014 and requires prompt veterinary attention and a committed management plan. Understanding the signs, how diagnosis works, and what treatment looks like can make a significant difference for an affected rat 1.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/diabetes-in-rats"},{"id":"Rabbits/getting-started/essential-supplies-for-rabbits","title":"Essential Supplies for Your Rabbit Companion","description":"Bringing a rabbit into your home is a long-term commitment, and providing the right supplies is the first step to ensuring a happy, healthy life for your new friend. Rabbits have specific needs that...","permalink":"/docs/Rabbits/getting-started/essential-supplies-for-rabbits"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/eye-health","title":"Eye Health and Vision Issues in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pig eyes are large, bright, and positioned on the sides of their head, giving them a wide field of vision to watch for predators. While generally robust, their eyes are susceptible to a range...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/eye-health"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fetal-arrhythmia","title":"Fetal Arrhythmia in Guinea Pigs: What It Is and What It Means","description":"Pregnancy in guinea pigs can be a delicate time, requiring close monitoring and appropriate veterinary care. One rare but important condition that can arise is fetal arrhythmia, an irregular heartbeat detected in a developing fetus. While unsettling to hear about, understanding this condition can help owners and rescues make informed decisions.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/fetal-arrhythmia"},{"id":"Rabbits/illnesses-and-conditions/fly-strike-in-rabbits","title":"Fly Strike (Myiasis) in Rabbits: A Veterinary Emergency","description":"Fly strike, also known as myiasis, is a devastating and rapidly progressing condition that is a true veterinary emergency. It occurs when flies, typically blowflies, lay eggs on a rabbit. These eggs...","permalink":"/docs/Rabbits/illnesses-and-conditions/fly-strike-in-rabbits"},{"id":"Rabbits/illnesses-and-conditions/gi-issues-in-rabbits","title":"GI Issues in Rabbits","description":"For rabbit owners, understanding and preventing gastrointestinal (GI) issues is paramount to ensuring the health and happiness of their beloved pets. Rabbits have delicate digestive systems, and...","permalink":"/docs/Rabbits/illnesses-and-conditions/gi-issues-in-rabbits"},{"id":"Chinchillas/illnesses-and-conditions/heartdisease","title":"Heart Disease and Heart Failure in Chinchillas","description":"Heart disease and heart failure are relatively uncommon in chinchillas but can still occur, especially as they age or due to certain genetic predispositions. These conditions can be challenging to detect early on, as chinchillas tend to hide their symptoms until the disease has progressed. Understanding the causes, signs, and treatments of heart disease in chinchillas is key to ensuring your pet remains healthy and receives proper care.","permalink":"/docs/Chinchillas/illnesses-and-conditions/heartdisease"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/home-health-care","title":"Home Health Care for Your Guinea Pig: A Helping All Little Things Guide","description":"Guinea pigs are hardy little creatures, but they rely on attentive caregivers to keep them healthy and comfortable. Performing regular home health checks is one of the most important things you can...","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/home-health-care"},{"id":"Rabbits/health-and-wellness/home-health-care-for-your-rabbit","title":"Home Health Care for Your Rabbit","description":"Caring for a rabbit can be a deeply rewarding experience, bringing joy and companionship to your home. These intelligent and social creatures, capable of living up to 12\u201315 years, thrive with proper care and attention [1]. Understanding their unique needs \u2014 from diet to dental health and disease prevention \u2014 is crucial for ensuring a long and happy life for your furry friend. This guide walks you through essential aspects of home health care for your rabbit.","permalink":"/docs/Rabbits/health-and-wellness/home-health-care-for-your-rabbit"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/lymphoma","title":"Lymphoma","description":"Lymphoma is a type of cancer that affects the lymphatic system, and while it may be rare in guinea pigs, it\u2019s a serious health condition that pet owners should be aware of. Early detection of lymphoma can significantly improve the chances of managing the disease and providing your guinea pig with a better quality of life. Understanding the nature of lymphoma, recognizing the early signs, and seeking timely veterinary care are crucial steps in ensuring the best possible outcome for your guinea pig.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/lymphoma"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/mycoplasma-in-rats","title":"Mycoplasma in Rats: An Essential Guide","description":"If you\'re a rat owner, you\'ve likely heard the term \'myco.\' Mycoplasma pulmonis is a species of bacteria that is the primary cause of chronic respiratory disease (CRD) in pet rats. It\'s a pervasive...","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/mycoplasma-in-rats"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/ovariancysts","title":"Ovarian Cysts","description":"Ovarian cysts are a common health issue in female guinea pigs, especially as they age. These fluid-filled sacs form on the ovaries and can lead to discomfort and health complications if untreated. Here\u2019s everything you need to know about detecting, treating, and preventing ovarian cysts in guinea pigs, as well as why the flank approach is often preferred for surgical removal.","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/illnesses-and-conditions/ovariancysts"},{"id":"Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/parasites-in-rats","title":"Parasites in Pet Rats","description":"Parasites are a relatively common health concern in pet rats and can affect even well-cared-for animals. Most infestations are highly treatable when caught early. This guide explains the types of parasites rats can carry, how to recognize them, how to treat them safely, and how to prevent future infestations.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/illnesses-and-conditions/parasites-in-rats"},{"id":"Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-dental-care","title":"Rat Dental Care Guide","description":"Dental health is one of the most important \u2014 and most overlooked \u2014 aspects of rat care. Because rat incisors grow continuously throughout life, they must wear down properly to prevent serious complications. A rat with dental problems will struggle to eat, lose weight rapidly, and can deteriorate quickly. Understanding how rat teeth work and how to support healthy dental wear is essential for every rat owner.","permalink":"/docs/Rats/health-and-wellness/rat-dental-care"},{"id":"Rabbits/health-and-wellness/rvhd2-vaccination","title":"The Importance of Vaccinating Your Rabbit Against RVHD2","description":"As a responsible rabbit owner, safeguarding your companion from preventable diseases is a top priority. One of the most serious threats to domestic rabbits today is Rabbit Hemorrhagic Disease Virus 2...","permalink":"/docs/Rabbits/health-and-wellness/rvhd2-vaccination"},{"id":"guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/urinary-bladder","title":"Urinary and Bladder Issues in Guinea Pigs","description":"Guinea pigs may be small, but they have complex needs\u2014and that includes their urinary health. Bladder and urinary tract issues are common in guinea pigs and can range from mild to life-threatening....","permalink":"/docs/guinea-pigs/health-and-wellness/urinary-bladder"}],"unlisted":false}}')}}]);